Here is the basic situation: You are in third seat, your partner opened 1@h or 1@s, 
and RHO does something other than pass.
Let's start with the simplest thing: your pard opens 1@h (say), and RHO doubles:  1@h - X - ??.

You have some support, say 3 cards, and some points -- Let's say between 6 and 9.
You would raise 1@h to 2@h with such a hand without the double, right? 
example: @sxx, @hQxx, @dKJxx, @cJxxx
Just raise to 2@h.
A ^*usingle raise^*n of 1@H or 1@S to 2M is exactly the same kind of hand you would raise wihtout the double.
That is the easy stuff.

Now, let's suppose you have a 4-card support.
If your hand is really weak (0 to 6 points), ^*uraise to 3^*n!!
I also insist on some shape (preferably a singleton somewhere), but I will do this with a doubleton in the other major, too.
Example:  1@h   (X)  and you have  @sxxx   @hQxxx   @dx   @cxxxxx 
Bid 3@h. Just do it!

Will you get doubled?  Maybe, but the defenders need trump tricks to be comfortable in doubling.
And if they can beat you a lot of tricks, they probably can make game on their own.|
