So we have covered 3 and 4 card raises.
What if you do not have a raise?
What if you do not have a fit and you do have a lot for points (say 10 or more)?
You ^*uREDOUBLE^*n
This says, "good hand, but no 4-card support.."
It is something you can find on the convention card under the box "redouble implies no fit" and is not alertable
You might have 3-card support, in which case you will raise later. 
But the redouble says, "we own the hand" and we expect to be able to punish the opponents if they get too frisky.

In principle, yes, it means no support. 
But what do you do with   @sxx   @hKxx   @dAxxx   @cAJ10x ?|
