at|^b@2
Conventionally, the auction 1@S/1@H - (X) - 2NT says, "I have at least a limit raise of your Major"
Because space may be limited, I think that 3-card support is also acceptable for the Jordan 2NT

BILAsst10: not everyone agrees - not saying right or wrong.
mitche: Eileen's point is well-taken. I use 2NT to show 3-card support with ruffing value.
Otherwise, the redouble gets overloaded.  We'll get to that in a moment.

Almost everyone uses the raise to 3 of a Major after X to show 4-card support and 0-6 HCP 
