at|mitche: Bidding:  Let's first look at 2@C.   North is passed hand, so his hand is limited. Therefore 2@C should not be 
4th suit forcing to game.  It should invite pard to make a natural bid, which could include 2@h with 3 cards in support.
Should North have bid 1@h over the double?  What other bids would you consider with North hand, if any? 
Let me list possible bids:  a) pass;  b) 1H;  c) XX;  d) 2 @C.
Pass is out of the question, and XX should be, too, since @SK singleton may be worthless. I think that with 
5 hearts, bidding 1@h would work if pard has support, and since we care about playing in Majors, bidding 1@h has the 
advantage of getting to that suit if it's  right. So 1@H has that going for it. |
