at|mitche:  The alternative, 2@C has the advantage of getting the defense off to the right start if East gets into the auction.
At the table I bid 1@h here.  The discussion is to get you to think why a bid might be better than an alternative auction.
azin: North could not bid 2@C as he hardly could count to 10 points.
mitche:  After the double, you do NOT need 10 points to bid at the 2 level.  With 10+ HCP, the correct action over 
a double is redouble.  You are telling opener your side has the balance of strength and should look for an opportunity 
to penalize the doubler''s side when they run from 1@D - X - XX, which you hope to make just on strength alone.
So 1@D  X  XX means a)we look for a chance to collect a fat penalty , or b)we are strong enough to look for game. |
